Curated by the Columbus Museum of Art \u2014 Raggin\u2019 On invites you to step inside Aminah\u2019s house and mind \u2014 to see what she saw, to feel what moved her. \n\nIt\u2019s a powerful gift for any art lover, a timeless keepsake for those who feel drawn to her work, and a table conversation piece that sparks thought, discussion, and reverence.\n\nCatch Aminah Robinson: Journeys Home, a \u25ab\ufe0f When Chiquita Mullins Lee\u2014literary artist, performer, and arts learning coordinator for the \u0040ohioartscouncil \u2014hosted the Springfield Museum of Art for Come Find Art, she was walking into more than an exhibit. She was stepping into legacy.  \u25ab\ufe0f Reflecting on her personal encounter with Aminah Robinson, she shared: \u201cEven though she\u2019s passed on from the earth, her influence is still powerful... she had such a bright, beautiful spirit.\u201d And on a more personal note, Chiquita reflected on what Aminah taught her as an artist: \u201cThat you can be prolific. You could just let the work pour out of you and not be stopped by anything.\u201d  \u25ab\ufe0f Aminah\u2019s creative fire was partly shaped by Elijah Pierce\u2014her mentor and one of the great self-taught artists of the 20th century. That legacy now continues through Chiquita\u2019s own work, including her co-authored children\u2019s book You Gotta Meet Mr. Pierce!, honoring the very man who inspired Aminah.  \u25ab\ufe0f To stand in a museum where those stories converge\u2014Aminah\u2019s art, Elijah\u2019s influence, and Chiquita\u2019s voice\u2014is to feel something sacred.\ud83d\udccd Aminah Robinson: Journeys Home, A Visual Memoir on view at the Springfield Museum of Art now until July 13th, 2025.  #ohioart #SMOA #aminah #aminahrobinson
